# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Box configuration — copy to `.env` and fill in.  Everything except the auth
#  token is OPTIONAL: with nothing else set, Box runs as a clean chat app that
#  drives Claude Code (and Codex, if installed) on this machine.
#
#  `./install.sh` creates this file for you and generates a token automatically.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# REQUIRED — the password you type to log into the web app. Keep it long & secret.
# If you leave this unset, the server generates a random one and writes it here on boot.
CC_AUTH_TOKEN=

# Port the Node server listens on (the tunnel / reverse-proxy points at this).
PORT=7321

# Default working directory new chats open in (and where project /skills are scanned).
# RECOMMENDED: point this at your main code directory. Defaults to $HOME, which works
# but is a poor place to work — claude shows a "launched in your home directory" notice
# and takes longer to become ready. ./install.sh asks for this interactively.
# CC_WORKSPACE=/home/youruser/code

# Your name — used in the per-session "morning brief" status doc the app maintains.
OWNER_NAME=you

# ── Voice (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Speech-to-text for the mic button. Leave both unset to disable voice.
#   ElevenLabs Scribe — zero-friction, multilingual.  https://elevenlabs.io
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
#   Deepgram nova-3 — higher-quality batch transcription.  https://deepgram.com
# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=

# ── Codex (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Codex chats appear automatically if the `codex` CLI is installed & logged in.
# Nothing to configure here.

# ── Linear board + "needs you" inbox (optional) ──────────────────────────────
# Set these to unlock the in-app Board tab and the "needs you" decision inbox.
# A free Linear personal account works fine.  Get an API key:
#   Linear → Settings → Security & access → Personal API keys.
# LINEAR_API_KEY=
#   LINEAR_TEAM_ID  = the team's GraphQL UUID (NOT the short key). The setup agent /
#                     concierge prompt can fetch this for you; or query the Linear API.
# LINEAR_TEAM_ID=
#   LINEAR_TEAM_KEY = the short team key shown on issues, e.g. "ENG" in ENG-123.
# LINEAR_TEAM_KEY=
#   NEEDS_LABEL     = the label that flags an issue as needing YOUR personal decision.
NEEDS_LABEL=needs-me

# ── Optional integrations used by some advanced features ─────────────────────
# GitHub token (so the Board can show / merge the PR linked to an issue).
# GITHUB_TOKEN=
# OpenAI key — powers the cheap per-session "morning brief" summariser. Without it,
# the brief feature is simply skipped (chat is unaffected).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://api.openai.com/v1
# BOX_ATTENTION_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# Optional: source secrets from an external env file instead of duplicating them here.
# EXTRA_ENV_FILE=/path/to/secrets.env

# Optional: a notes/"brain" directory (markdown). If it contains a meetings/ subdir
# it powers the Pipelines tab; otherwise harmless.
# BRAIN_DIR=/home/youruser/brain
